Package edu.umn.nlpie.mtap.model

Interface LabelIndex<L extends Label>

Type Parameters:
L - The label type.
All Superinterfaces:
java.util.Collection<@NotNull L>, java.lang.Iterable<L>
All Known Implementing Classes:
DistinctLabelIndex, StandardLabelIndex
public interface LabelIndex<L extends Label>
extends java.util.Collection<@NotNull L>
An immutable collection of labels ordered by their location in text. By default sorts by ascending Label.getStartIndex() and then by ascending Label.getEndIndex().

  • Method Details

    • isDistinct

      boolean isDistinct()
      Returns whether or not the index is distinct.

      Index distinctness is based on whether the labels in the index can overlap or cannot overlap. In the case of distinct, non-overlapping labels optimization can be made to the process of searching for labels, as well as iteration over and size computation of sub-indices.

      Returns:
      Returns true if the index is distinct, false if the index is not distinct.
